# Local debug stack (pointer)

The full runbook lives in [`.claude/skills/local-debug/SKILL.md`](../../.claude/skills/local-debug/SKILL.md)
— read it before starting, driving, or debugging the local stack. It covers:

- Startup order & ports: `docker compose up -d` (Postgres + MeritRank + Hasura
  + MinIO) → `./scripts/run-server-local.sh` (console, foreground) →
  `./scripts/run-flutter-web-local.sh` (debug dartdevc on :8888, no WASM) →
  `caddy run --config Caddyfile.local` → open https://dev.lvh.me:9443.
- QA login/signup bypass via `.env` `QA_*` params (`test-login`,
  `/_qa/latest-email`, email-sink files) — never script the real email flow.
- Direct state setup / action triggering: API v2 + session access-token,
  Hasura admin GraphQL & remote-schema reload, `psql` into the compose
  Postgres (MeritRank caveats).
- Playwright driving notes (Flutter semantics, no DOM text input, cache traps).

Non-negotiable even without reading the runbook: **never** start the server
with a bare `dart run bin/tentura.dart` (wrong port + default JWT keys →
`JWSInvalidSignature`); always use `scripts/run-server-local.sh`, and never
background it with `nohup`/`&`.
